description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the new mental health contract that TEWV were successfully awarded in 2020, there is an opportunity for 2 Clinical Leads to join the team at HMP Northumberland. HMP Northumberland is a category C prison in the North East of England. This is an exciting opportunity to be part of a dynamic and evolving team in a rewarding environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to be; innovative, flexible and able to engage clients with complex needs. Strong team working principles are essential and you will network with a variety of people as well as work in partnership with a range of different agencies both internal and external to the prison.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for experienced clinicians to join a busy team working in a rewarding environment where you will get to practice a full range of psychiatric nursing interventions. You will be required to have strong skills in the management of a caseload, coordinate and plan care for those with complex needs and work autonomously making decisions based on comprehensive mental health and risk assessment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require the post holders to be committed to equal opportunities and non-discriminatory practices and reflect the trust values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A visit to the prison or an informal discussion about the post is encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kate Muter, Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kate.muter@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01670 383541&lt;/p&gt;
